---
import IdeasSidebar from "../../components/IdeasSidebar.astro";
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>mosops — Operators you can see, edit, and redeploy while they run</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="mosops is a mosaigo distribution for building Kubernetes, Podman, and Docker operators as live pipeline graphs. Sub-second inner loop. Real clusters. No YAML archaeology."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/hub-subproject.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="hub-subproject">
    <IdeasSidebar active="mosops" />

    <div class="hub-main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hub-status-row">
          <span class="hub-chip draft">🧊 Draft — concept only</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">mosaigo distribution</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">Kubernetes · Podman · Docker</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">Live Studio</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Operators you can <span class="accent">see, edit, and redeploy</span> while they run.</h1>
        <p class="tagline">mosops turns Kubernetes controllers into mosaigo pipelines. Informers, reconcilers, clients, webhooks, leaders, finalizers — each a reusable step. The graph is the operator. The inner loop is sub-second. The same framework builds operators for Kubernetes, Podman, and Docker.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="intent-callout">
          <h3>Intent</h3>
          <p>Writing a Kubernetes operator should feel like authoring a pipeline, not reinventing informers and workqueues for the fifth time. <strong>mosops attacks four specific pains:</strong> the 30–60 second inner loop, opaque execution you can't step through, boilerplate every team rewrites, and the Go-only gatekeeping that keeps operators out of reach for most teams. Studio makes the reconcile waterfall visible. Hot-swap makes iteration instant. The step library makes the second operator trivial.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">The idea in one picture</div>
        <h2>Informer → reconcile → client → status, as a graph</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every arrow is a topic. Every box is a step you can inspect, edit, swap, and hot-reload — with the controller still running against a real cluster.</p>
        <div class="pipe-diagram">Informer ──┐
           ├─→ workqueue ─→ reconcile.dispatch ─→ reconcile.step(s) ─→ client.apply
Webhook ───┘                                              ↓
                                                  condition.set → status.patch
                                                          ↓
                                                  metrics + k8s.event.record</div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Design principles</div>
        <h2>Six things mosops holds firm</h2>
        <div class="diff-grid">
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon primary">🕸️</div>
            <h3>The pipeline graph is the operator</h3>
            <p>No main.go-as-controller. A reconcile loop is a named pipeline with named steps. That's what Studio renders. That's what hot-reload swaps.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon accent">⚡</div>
            <h3>Sub-second inner loop</h3>
            <p>Edit a reconcile step, save, and the live controller hot-swaps it without losing informer state, leader lease, or workqueue position.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon success">🎯</div>
            <h3>Real clusters, not mocks</h3>
            <p>Develop against actual clusters from day one. Studio captures reconcile waterfalls so you can replay any decision the controller made.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon light">🔌</div>
            <h3>Multi-backend, one shape</h3>
            <p><code>client.kubernetes</code>, <code>client.podman</code>, <code>client.docker</code> present the same interface. An operator targeting one can target another by swapping one step.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon error">🧱</div>
            <h3>Lifecycle built-in</h3>
            <p>Finalizers, leader election, webhooks, conditions, events, rate-limited workqueues — first-class steps, not copy-pasted snippets from a five-year-old sample repo.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon muted">🧩</div>
            <h3>Coexist with Kubebuilder</h3>
            <p>mosops is not a rewrite of controller-runtime. Existing Kubebuilder projects can drop mosops pipelines into their reconcile funcs incrementally.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Step library (target)</div>
        <h2>Informers, clients, leaders, webhooks</h2>
        <div class="pkg-grid">
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">informer.watch.resource</div><div class="pkg-desc">Typed informer publishing Add/Update/Delete topics</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">workqueue.rate.limited</div><div class="pkg-desc">Rate-limited, deduped work queue</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">reconcile.dispatch</div><div class="pkg-desc">Fetch object, branch by phase, emit to reconcile pipeline</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">reconcile.step</div><div class="pkg-desc">Base class for user reconcile logic</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">client.kubernetes</div><div class="pkg-desc">Kubernetes API client resource</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">client.podman</div><div class="pkg-desc">Podman API client with same interface</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">client.docker</div><div class="pkg-desc">Docker engine client, same interface</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">leader.elect.k8s</div><div class="pkg-desc">Lease-based leader election gate</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">webhook.validate</div><div class="pkg-desc">Admission webhook as a pipeline</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">webhook.mutate</div><div class="pkg-desc">Mutating admission as a pipeline</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">condition.set</div><div class="pkg-desc">Merge Ready/Progressing/Degraded conditions</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">finalizer.ensure</div><div class="pkg-desc">Add/remove finalizer with retry</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">status.patch</div><div class="pkg-desc">Safe status subresource patch</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">k8s.event.record</div><div class="pkg-desc">Emit Kubernetes Event for object</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">metrics.publish.prometheus</div><div class="pkg-desc">/metrics endpoint with reconcile histograms</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">crd.generate</div><div class="pkg-desc">Emit CRD manifests from Go types at build</div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-centered">
        <div class="section-label">The inner loop</div>
        <h2>Hot-swap a reconcile step without losing state</h2>
        <p class="section-desc" style="max-width:720px;">You edit a step. mosops rebuilds it, pauses the workqueue, swaps the step, resumes — all without dropping informer caches, surrendering the leader lease, or losing in-flight work. The reconcile waterfall in Studio shows exactly which step ran, what it read, what it wrote, and what it returned. The inner loop is measured in <strong>hundreds of milliseconds</strong>, not tens of seconds.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-centered">
        <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
        <h2>A mosaigo distribution for controllers</h2>
        <div class="arch-visual">
          <div class="arch-layer accent">
            mosops <span class="desc">Informers · reconcilers · clients · leaders · webhooks · CRD gen</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer deep">
            mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine · topics · last-value · Studio · hot-swap · config</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="arch-caption">mosops introduces no new primitives. Informers are resources. Reconcilers are pipelines. Hot-swap comes from the engine.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
        <h2>From informer to Kubebuilder coexistence</h2>
        <div class="principle-grid">
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">01</div><div><h4>Informer + reconcile on a real CRD</h4><p>Watch a toy CRD, dispatch to a reconcile pipeline, patch status. Prove end-to-end on a kind cluster.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">02</div><div><h4>Scaffold + packaging</h4><p><code>mosops new operator</code> generates a pipeline skeleton, CRD types, Dockerfile, and deployment manifest.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">03</div><div><h4>Studio resource tree + reconcile waterfall</h4><p>Browse cluster resources. Click an object. See its last reconcile as a waterfall of step inputs/outputs.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">04</div><div><h4>Pipeline editor + hot-reload</h4><p>Edit reconcile steps in Studio or on disk. Live swap without losing informer state, leader lease, or workqueue.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">05</div><div><h4>Leaders, finalizers, webhooks</h4><p>Full lifecycle support. Admission webhooks as pipelines. Finalizer choreography as first-class steps.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">06</div><div><h4>Podman + Docker backends</h4><p>Same reconcile pipelines, different <code>client.*</code> step. A mosops operator that runs against Kubernetes today runs against Podman tomorrow.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">07</div><div><h4>Kubebuilder coexistence</h4><p>Drop a mosops pipeline into an existing controller-runtime Reconcile func. Incremental adoption path.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

